Program: Count Even and Odd Numbers in an Array
This Java program reads an array of integers from the user and counts the number of even and odd elements in it.

import java.util.*;
public class Countevenodd {

	public static void main(String[] args) {
		// TODO Auto-generated method stub
		Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
		System.out.println("Enter size of array: ");
		int n =sc.nextInt();
		int[] arr = new int[n];
		System.out.println("Enter array elements: ");
		for(int i=0;i<n;i++) {
			arr[i] = sc.nextInt();
		}
		int c_e = 0;
		int c_o = 0;
		for(int i=0;i<n;i++) {
			if(arr[i]%2 == 0) {
				c_e++;
			}
			else {
				c_o++;
			}
		}
		System.out.println("No.of of even numbers: "+c_e);
		System.out.println("No.of of even numbers: "+c_o);
	}

}


Sample Input/Output:
Enter size of array: 
6
Enter array elements: 
1 2 3 4 5 6
No.of of even numbers: 3
No.of of even numbers: 3
